  "prompt": "When I eat sushi, what is the eel sauce made of?",
  "response": "Eel sauce, also known as \"nitsume\" or \"unagi no tare,\" is a sweet and savory sauce commonly used in Japanese cuisine, especially with sushi. It is traditionally made from a few key ingredients:\n\n1. **Soy Sauce**: The base of the sauce, providing a salty umami flavor.\n2. **Sugar**: Adds sweetness, balancing the salty soy sauce.\n3. **Mirin**: A sweet rice wine that adds depth and richness to the flavor.\n4. **Sake**: Sometimes included for additional complexity.\n\nThe ingredients are typically simmered together until thickened to create a syrupy consistency. The sauce is often drizzled over grilled eel (unagi) but can also be used to enhance the flavor of various sushi and other dishes.",
